review_blob: 50 cl. bottle. Cloudy white with long head. light aroma in nose. A little body with a little bitterness. A mainstream wheat
50 cl. bottle. Copper with a creamy long head. Hops and Lemon in nose. Medium body with good aroma. Good strong bitterness. A powerfull IPA, but a little more body would be nice. A very decent IPA
50 cl. Bottle. Amber with long foam/ head.  Flower,fruitand hops in nose. Medium - strong bitterness. okay harmony but the bitterness diminate a little.

50 cl. bottle. Black with long foam. Coffee and liquorice aroma. Mild chocolate aroma and taste. Creamy and with strong bitterness in the aftertaste.
Very good harmony
